 :tx/rationale "DOG-FOOD SESSION 026 — FRICTION ASSESSMENT (in-progress). POSITIVE: (1) braid task create with long titles auto-extracts BACKGROUND/ACCEPTANCE into separate datoms — this is genuinely useful, I can write rich task specs in a single command. (2) braid write assert with -d flag for setting task attributes works well for L2/L3 detail. (3) braid task dep add works reliably for wiring dependency graphs. (4) braid observe captures design insights immediately — the store IS my working memory. (5) The -q flag is essential — without it, the M(t) footer on every command would be overwhelming during bulk task creation. (6) PSR (proactive spec retrieval) surfaced relevant topology specs during task creation — spec IS an active participant. NEGATIVE: (1) Task list truncation is STILL the biggest friction point — I created 27 tasks and cannot verify them via braid task list because titles are invisible. I had to use raw Datalog queries to audit my own tasks. This is the #1 UX priority. (2) braid task set for setting background FAILED silently — I had to discover that write assert -d is the correct path. The command surface is confusing: task set vs write assert for the same entity. (3) No braid task show --short flag — I want to see title + background + acceptance as labeled sections. Currently task show dumps the raw title blob. (4) Harvest warnings are TOO AGGRESSIVE — 44 txns since harvest triggers warnings on every single command. During bulk task creation (27 tasks + 17 deps = 44 txns), every command shows the warning. Need a quiet-during-batch mode or higher threshold. (5) Cannot search tasks by content — no braid task search command. I had to use Datalog queries to find my own tasks."
